article.headline: Stetson 85, Palm Beach Atlantic 67
article.story: DELAND, Fla. -- Tyshawn Patterson and A.J. Smith each scored 20 points to lead Stetson to an 85-67 victory over Palm Beach Atlantic on Wednesday. Patterson scored half of his 20 points in the first 13 minutes to help Stetson build a 35-15 lead. Smith scored 10 points in each half. Ridge Graham added 19 points in only 22 minutes for Stetson (2-3). Graham connected on 7 of 9 shots from the field and 5 of 6 free throws. Stetson dominated Palm Beach Atlantic (1-4) early and was never threatened. The Hatters scored the first eight points and led 49-23 at the half. Palm Beach Atlantic's Jonathan Lawrence had 18 points, followed by Chris Joseph with 14 and Dante Valentine with 10. Palm Beach Atlantic coach Terry Primm received two technical fouls and was ejected with 7:11 left in the game.
